          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 15068,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Despite the input of EU directives, legal provisions are often formulated in general terms, which makes it difficult for SMEs to apply them. As a result, professionals face difficulties in translating these general principles into operational decisions for the design of interfaces, software or infrastructure.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s8",
          "section_path": [
            "Contribution of CPME",
            "(2) COMBATING REGULATORY FRAGMENTATION"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 45,
          "char_len": 310
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p23",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Influencer Marketing",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "France adopted a law on *influencers* regulating their commercial practices and prohibiting certain advertising (aesthetic surgery, sports betting)."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 10154,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "In the absence of a sufficiently precise European framework, some Member States have taken the initiative to legislate to close loopholes in areas of consumer protection. By way of illustration, in 2023 France adopted a law on *influencers* regulating their commercial practices and prohibiting certain advertising (aesthetic surgery, sports betting). This national legislation could have been extended at European level in order not to participate in the fragmentation of the single market.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s8",
          "section_path": [
            "Contribution of CPME",
            "(2) COMBATING REGULATORY FRAGMENTATION"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 72,
          "char_len": 491
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p24",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 8803,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "However, it is essential to stress that the EU already has an advanced rulebook in this area. The *future Digital Fairness Act* should not add regulatory complexity but contribute to this effort to simplify standards. In particular, it must fill the interpretative gaps arising from the multiplication of texts. Any European standards should also encourage and take account of the many self-regulatory initiatives that already exist today (particularly in the field of digital marketing), some of which involve public or semi-public authorities, in accordance with the principle laid down in the Audiovisual Media Services Directive.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s8",
          "section_path": [
            "Contribution of CPME",
            "(2) COMBATING REGULATORY FRAGMENTATION"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 95,
          "char_len": 633
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p25",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3889,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Thus, the *Digital Fairness Act* must take the form of a regulation rather than a directive. The advantage of the Regulation is that it is directly applicable in similar terms and sets clear obligations and prohibitions.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s8",
          "section_path": [
            "Contribution of CPME",
            "(2) COMBATING REGULATORY FRAGMENTATION"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 36,
          "char_len": 220
